overview.eaover:
For more information about EnviroAtlas data, go to https://www.epa.gov/enviroatlas/enviroatlas-fact-sheets. 

With the exception of poverty level data, these values were extracted from the 2010 Census SF1 Tables. The poverty level attributes (PLx2_Pop and PLx2_Pct) come from the American Community Survey 5-year estimates for 2006-2010. 

The "applicable block group population" value used in the calculation of the PLx2 attributes represents the "Population for whom poverty level statistics were calculated." According to the Census Bureau, this excludes people living in "group quarters" such as dormitories and elderly living communities. 

The following values were incorporated into the attributes: 

